    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="[November 2020, Cox's Bazar] Protection trends and situation analysis : Housing, Land and Property Task Forum (HLPTF) • Host communities continue to be the primary providers of land for refugees, particularly in the Teknaf camps. This has led to precarious tenure arrangements, with refugees paying rent from a low of zero in the older camps to a high of 500-800 BDT per month in the Teknaf camps. The majority are paying rent through CFW, in-kind (through food rations, NFI materials), and labour (working on fishing boats and agricultural farms owned by the host communities). There has been a marked increase in exploitative practises, with those who cannot pay the high rent resorting to negative coping mechanisms, including illicit activities/yaba, sexual favours/trafficking—leading to many living in constant fear of eviction and homelessness."/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 39 52 65 78 91 104 117 130 143 156 169 182 195 208 221 234 247 260 273 286 299 312 325 338 351 364 377 390 403 416 429 442 455 468 481 494 507 520 533 546 559 572 585 598 611 624 637 650 663 676 689 702 715 728 741 754 767 780 793 806 819 832 845 858 871 884 897 910 923 936 949 962 975 988 1001 1014 1027 1040 1053 1066 1079 1092 1105 1118 1131 1144 1157 1170 1183 1196 1209 1222 1235 1248 1261 1274 1287 1300 1313 1326 1339 1352 1365 1378 1391 1404 1417 1430 1443 1456 1469 1482 1495 1508 1521 1534 1547 1560 1573 1586 1599 1612 1625 1638 1651 1664 1677 1690 1703 1716 1729 1742 1755 1768 1781 1794 1807 1820 1833 1846 1859 1872 1885 1898 1911 1924 1937 1950 1963 1976 1989 2002 2015 2028 2041 2054 2067 2080 2093 2131 2106 2111 2116 2121 2126 2164 2171 2178 2185 2136 2143 2150 2157 2192 2199 2195 2202 2206 2219"/>
